name: Bandage
desc: A weak heal.

name: Tend Wounds
desc: You take a break from combat to tend your wounds.

name: Swing
desc: The most basic of attacks. No special features, this is a threat to only the weakest of foes.

name: Taunt
desc: The mages would have you know that sometimes words are more powerful than weapons. Stun your enemy, but deal no damage.

name: Slice
desc: Twisting your weapon mid-strike creates a jagged wound, bleeding your foe.

name: Uppercut
desc: Hit your foe with a brutal uppercut, stunning them.

name: Lacerate
desc: Use your warrior's training to hit a vital artery, bleeding your foe.

name: Juggernaut Strike
desc: Smash your for with a heavy, debilitating strike.

name: Fireball
desc: Baby's First Spell. Does minor damage, but also sets target on fire.

name: Immolate
desc: Set your foe alight, dealing massive degen damage.

name: Fireblast
desc: Blasts your foe with scorching flames.

name: Inferno
desc: Summon the very fiercest of flames around your foe, scorching them.

name: Meteor
desc: Utilizing your mastery over the arcane, you call down a meteor to obliterate your foe.

name: Chill
desc: Invoking the north winds, you chill the air around a foe, dealing damage.

name: Icy Blast
desc: Blast your foe with ice. Heal yourself for a small amount.

name: Frostbite
desc: You call forth the very worst of the mountain winds, freezing and degening your foe.

name: Curse
desc: Calling upon the... less than savory gods, you invoke eldritch energies upon a foe.

name: Contaminate
desc: Toss a flask of nasty chemicals at your foe, poisoning them and causing moderate degen.

name: Putrid Curse
desc: The warlocks would tell you that the natural state of everything is death. They'd also tell you that they're merely speeding up the process.

name: Frighten
desc: Conjure frightening images in your enemy's mind, stunning them and dealing damage.

name: Terrify
desc: There are some things that the mortal mind is not meant to see. Terrify your enemy, stunning them and using their fear to feed your lifeforce.

name: Vampiric Bite
desc: Somehow, you use your weapon in such a way that it steals life. Not sure how that works.

name: Rip Life
desc: Your mastery of the vampiric arts allows you to siphon your enemy's lifeforce, adding it to your own.

name: Smite
desc: The novice priests use this spell to clean up vermin. Be happy you're not considered vermin.

name: Divine Blessing
desc: The power of the Gods restores you and smites your enemies.

name: Censor
desc: Call the power of the heavens to silence your enemy, stunning them and dealing damage. Your conviction renews you slightly.

name: Divine Hammer
desc: Your faith allows you to conjure an ethereal hammer to strike your enemies, healing you and stunning them

name: Cleanse
desc: You pray to the holy ones, asking their salvation. Removes 2 degen effects from you.

name: Divine Judgement
desc: Call down the wrath of the divines to smite your foe, burning them in the process.

name: Restore
desc: Your conviction heals and restores you. Removes 2 degen effects from you.

name: Divine Shockwave
desc: Invoking awesome powers, the priesthood calls down the divine judgement of the Gods. Such devotion is rewarded, as you're healed for a small amount.

name: Mind Sap
desc: The same spell that caused the original Aetherists to be banished from the Sorcerer guilds, Mind Sap drains the very energy of a foe. Drain a small amount of energy.

name: Counter
desc: Those who have fought against the Aetherists have reported their horrifying ability to reflect the attacks of their enemies. In short, the Aetherist allows their enemy to destroy themselves.

name: Reflect
desc: Few reports have returned of the use of this skill in battle - mainly because those who face it don't return themselves - but for those that do, the accounts of the Aetherists forcing their enemies to annihilate themselves are enough to cause armies to turn tail and run. Reflect damage and gain a small amount of regeneration.

name: Misjudgement
desc: The righteous wrath of paladins and sorcerers bears no threat to the trained Aetherist. Reflect either fire or holy damage.

name: Deny Curse
desc: Rather than invoking some holy wrath, or pathetically attempting to heal through damage, the Aetherist simply reflects the curses of their enemy. Reflect either dark or poison damage.

name: Yeti's Curse
desc: The cold, avalanche-prone lands of the north bear no threat to the trained Aetherist. Reflect either ice or physical damage.

name: Rip Thoughts
desc: Rip the very energy from your foe. Steals a medium amount of energy.

name: Mind Rend
desc: The experienced Aetherist can cripple a foe by draining them of huge amounts of energy. Steals a large amount of energy.
